{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, the bias on behalf of the most popular view (for more indecisive voters) may appear troublesome, as there is no guarantee that popular views (1) serve the interest of the particular voter;",
    "(2) track a desirable electoral outcome.",
    "The advent of new polling methods potentially allows for a bias corrector, by introducing the possibility of knowing with a great deal of precision what others whom one identifies think-and conversely, what others with whom one does not want to be associated think.",
    "Call this group endorsement (Lau and Redlawsk 2001).",
    "The mechanism is simple: you refer to the judgment of a trusted other, for example, a social group that you identify with."
  ]
}